POSIX Character Classes

Character Class 	Description
[:alnum:]			The alphanumeric characters; in ASCII, equivalent to [A-Za-z0-9]
[:word:] 			The same as [:alnum:] with the addition of the _ character
[:alpha:] 			Alphabetical, equiv to [A-Za-z]
[:blank:]			Includes teh space and tab characters
[:cntrl:] 			The ASCII control codes
[:digit:] 			Numerals 0 through 9
[:graph:] 			The visible characters; in ASCII, includes characters 33 through 126
[:lower:] 			The lowercase letters
[:punct:] 			The punctuation characters in ASCII
[:print:] 			The printable characters; all [:graph:] characters plus space
[:space:] 			The whitespace characters including , space, tab carriage return, newline, vertical tab and form feed.
[:upper:] 			The uppercase characters
[:xdigit:]  		Characters used to express hexadecimal numbers; in ASCII, equivalent to [A-Fa-f0-9]

